OL,3,CWhat do we know about the Ebola
OL,4,Coutbreak and what is the risk to the
OL,5,CUK?
OL,7,FWhat is Ebola and why is this strain
OL,8,Fparticularly concerning?
OL,10,FThere are six known virus species that
OL,11,Fcan lead to Ebola, but only three
OL,12,Fcause most large outbreaks: Ebola
OL,13,Fvirus, Sudan virus and Bundibugyo
OL,14,Fvirus.
OL,16,FThe latest epidemic is driven by the
OL,17,Flatter, the less common Bundibugyo
OL,18,Fvirus, for which there is currently no
OL,19,Fcure and no licensed vaccines.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779109902
OL,3,CWhat do we know about the Ebola
OL,4,Coutbreak and what is the risk to the
OL,5,CUK?
OL,7,FThere are also no vaccines in late-
OL,8,Fstage clinical development that could
OL,9,Fbe readily deployed during the
OL,10,Foutbreak.
OL,12,FAlthough more than 20 Ebola outbreaks
OL,13,Fhave taken place in Congo and Uganda,
OL,14,Fthis is only the third time that the
OL,15,FBundibugyo virus has been detected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
