OL,3,CWhat do we know about the Ebola
OL,4,Coutbreak and what is the risk to the
OL,5,CUK?
OL,7,FSymptoms of Ebola often include fever,
OL,8,Ffatigue, muscle pain, headache and a
OL,9,Fsore throat, followed by vomiting,
OL,10,Fdiarrhoea, abdominal pain, among
OL,11,Fothers.
OL,13,FInternal and external bleeding can
OL,14,Foccur later as the disease progresses.
OL,16,FThe incubation period of Ebola ranges
OL,17,Ffrom two to 21 days, with an average
OL,18,Fof eight to 10 days.
OL,20,FWhere is the outbreak and how many
OL,21,Fpeople have tested positive?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
