OL,3,CWhat do we know about the Ebola
OL,4,Coutbreak and what is the risk to the
OL,5,CUK?
OL,7,FThis is a concerning outbreak for
OL,8,Fseveral reasons, according to Dr
OL,9,FDaniela Manno, Clinical Assistant
OL,10,FProfessor at the London School of
OL,11,FHygiene & Tropical Medicine (LSHTM).
OL,13,FDr Manno said "transmission may have
OL,14,Fbeen ongoing for several weeks before
OL,15,Fthe outbreak was formally recognised"
OL,16,Fand that the outbreak is occurring in
OL,17,F"a region affected by insecurity,
OL,18,Fpopulation displacement, and high
OL,19,Fpopulation mobility, all of which can
OL,20,Fcomplicate surveillance, contact
OL,21,Ftracing, and delivery of healthcare".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779109902
OL,3,CWhat do we know about the Ebola
OL,4,Coutbreak and what is the risk to the
OL,5,CUK?
OL,7,FPrevious Ebola outbreaks in the region
OL,8,Fhave lasted as long as two years.
OL,10,FHowever, it is not uncommon in the
OL,11,Fregion, and Dr Manno says the outbreak
OL,12,Fresponse capacity has gotten stronger.
OL,14,FWhy is it a global health emergency?
OL,16,FA Public Health Emergency of
OL,17,FInternational Concern (PHEIC) is the
OL,18,Fhighest level of international public
OL,19,Fhealth alert that WHO can declare
OL,20,Funder the International Health
OL,21,FRegulations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779109902
OL,3,CWhat do we know about the Ebola
OL,4,Coutbreak and what is the risk to the
OL,5,CUK?
OL,7,FHowever, experts highlight that this
OL,8,Fdoes that the outbreak is globally
OL,9,Funcontrollable.
OL,11,FDr Amanda Rojek, Associate Professor
OL,12,Fof Health Emergencies at the
OL,13,FUniversity of Oxford, said: "The
OL,14,Fdeclaration of a PHEIC does not
OL,15,Fimmediately change the reality on the
OL,16,Fground. What it does do is signal to
OL,17,Fthe international community the need
OL,18,Fto pay attention to this outbreak and
OL,19,Fsupport a well-coordinated response."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
